RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 1 6F All Weather Track CR: 87. Claiming Purse 20000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since August 15 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500, if for $10,500, allowed 2 lbs. (Maiden, Claiming And Starter Races For $10,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DINOS DIXIE was sent leaving the break and assumed command, set a solid early pace into the turn, extended the lead while well handled approaching the quarter marker, kicked clear into the stretch, was kept to task into the final sixteenth while maintaining a clear lead and was hand urged to the wire to win convincingly. RESPOND tracked the solid early pace from the inside, chased DINOS DIXIE to the quarter marker, tipped two wide into the stretch, could not match strides with DINOS DIXIE at the furlong marker, finished evenly in the final sixteenth and was second best in the end. LASMUIGH (GB) was allowed to settle early on, saved ground along the turn and advanced approaching the quarter pole, maintained an inside position into the stretch, could not impact the top pair in the final furlong, finished evenly and held for third. STRENGTH OF AUTISM was prominent in the early running, stalked the decent pace from a two wide path into the turn, chased two wide into the stretch, lost position at the furlong marker, weakened in the final stages and was outfinished for third. WEE BEASTIE chased the decent early pace from a two wide position, swung three wide into the stretch and tired in the final furlong. IN HONOR OF AUTISM tracked the decent early pace from the outside, came three wide to the quarter marker and was coaxed along four wide into the stretch, could not keep pace approaching the furlong grounds and gave way.

ENTRY.NAME: Wee Beastie
ENTRY.OWNER: Fishbough William L and Fishbough-Miller Alyxandria

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 2 5 1/2F All Weather Track CR: 84. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 15500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $4,000 OR LESS IN 2022 - 2023 OR CLAIMING PRICE $8,000. Three Year Olds, 123 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SHEZA GIRLY GIRL tracked the solid early pace while between rivals, raced two wide into the turn, shifted to the three path approaching the top of the lane, came a in bit tight in upper stretch while between runners, responded to urging inside of the furlong marker, finished well in deep stretch, caught AUSTRAIN NAVY in the final strides and edged away to prevail at the finish. AUSTRIAN NAVY was asked for speed leaving the start and gained command in the early running, set a solid pace into the turn, drew to a clear lead along the bend, was well handled to the quarter marker and held foes at bay to the top of the stretch, extended the lead at the furlong grounds, was kept to task under steady urging to the sixteenth-marker, could not hold off the winner in deep stretch and just held for second at the wire. TRULY FABULOUS was allowed to settle in the early going while not far back, tracked outside of rivals along the turn and was roused four wide into the stretch, rallied while widest in the final sixteenth, just missed for second at the finish and was up in time to secure the nod for third. GET'EM TIGER tracked the early pace from the outside, came three wide into the turn then gave chase two wide into the stretch, chased to the furlong marker, was gaining in the late stages but needed more in deep stretch and was outfinished for the minor awards. THREAD COUNT close up in the early stages, took back to track from the inside, saved ground into the stretch, lost position at the furlong pole and weakened. SPUN BEAUTIFUL was bumped and crowded by neighboring runners at the start and was away a step slowly, rushed into contention early and tracked the pace into the turn, chased two wide to the quarter marker, could not keep pace heading to mid-stretch and tired.

ENTRY.NAME: Sheza Girly Girl
ENTRY.OWNER: Finder Gary Grasso Joseph and Smith Laurie

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 3 1M Turf CR: 98. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 32000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON $15,000 TWICE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR STATE BRED OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $62,500. Three Year Olds, 123 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since August 15 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $62,500 (Maiden, Claiming And Starter Races For $50,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LADYWEARSTHERING broke well but was content to cede the early pacesetting duties to MADEIRA WINE, then put some pressure on halfway down the backstretch while racing two deep to the far turn, responded when roused at the top of the stretch and wore down that rival passing the eighth pole with enough in reserve to hold off a fast closing challenger to the outside. SIGNORINA MERISI (GB) settled off the two leaders while racing in the three path under a stout hold, was asked to pick it up near the three furlong marker and responded, entered the stretch in the three path and produced a strong late run but came up short. CLOCKSTRIKESTWELVE settled along the inside, inched closer heading to the quarter marker, rallied into upper stretch and came within aim at the furlong marker, needed more in the late stages, was outkicked and held safely for third, . MADEIRA WINE broke from the gate intent on getting to the front, gained the lead going into the first turn then was allowed to set sensible fractions, met a challenge by LADYWEARSTHERING heading into the stretch, held on to mid-stretch then gave way. ASSIGNATION broke outward at the start then was devoid of early speed, raced three to four wide at the back of the field through the clubhouse turn and down the backstretch, made a four to five wide rally through the far then then flattened out in the stretch. A CROWN FOR KITTEN was not asked for speed in the early stages, settled near the back of the pack racing in the two path, inched closer heading into the far turn, was asked in earnest at the quarter pole then raced on the wrong lead down the stretch and was unable to improve position.

ENTRY.NAME: Ladywearsthering
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke well, stalked 2d to far turn, bid 1/4, wore down rival

ENTRY.NAME: Signorina Merisi (GB)
ENTRY.OWNER: Charles, Ronald L. and Gordon, Samuel
ENTRY.COMMENT: settled 3-wide, bid 5/16, good late run, second best

ENTRY.NAME: Madeira Wine
ENTRY.COMMENT: set pressured but sensible fractions, gave way late

ENTRY.NAME: A Crown for Kitten
ENTRY.COMMENT: settled 2p near back, bid 1/4, on wrong lead stretch run

ENTRY.NAME: Assignation
ENTRY.COMMENT: trailed early, circled field far turn, flattened out stretch

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 4 5 1/2F All Weather Track CR: 93. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 15500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $4,000 OR LESS IN 2022 - 2023 OR CLAIMING PRICE $8,000. Three Year Olds, 123 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since August 15 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000 (Maiden , Claiming And Starter Races For $3,500 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BOSS OF THEMOSS was hustled away from the start, contested the early pace with RALLY CAT and showed speed into the turn, carved out fast fractions along the turn while pressed to the quarter marker, shook free into the stretch and extended the lead at the furlong marker, responded to urging and held foes at bay to the sixteenth-marker, met the bid of GRIT AND CURIOSITY into deep stretch, dug in in the final strides and lasted at the finish for a determined win. GRIT AND CURIOSITY was away in good order, tracked the fast early pace between runners, improved position on the turn while three wide, continued to gain three wide into the stretch, rallied while on the left lead in the final sixteenth, pressured the winner in the final strides but could not get by the determined BOSS OF THEMOSS and was clear for second. REFI NOW tracked the fast early pace while two wide and between runners, raced a bit in tight while two wide nearing the top of the stretch, ran evenly to the furlong marker, was outkicked by the top pair in deep stretch, ran on in the final yards and just held for third at the wire. SUMMANUS chased the fast early pace from the outside, improved position four wide on the turn, drifted out a bit at the top of the lane and lost ground heading to the furlong marker, re-rallied in the final sixteenth and just missed for third at the finish. RALLY CAT was asked for speed away from the start and disputed the fast early pace with BOSS OF THEMOSS, pressed from the three path into the turn and shifted to the two path nearing the quarter marker, lost position into the stretch and chased to the furlong grounds, lacked a response in deep stretch and tired. THE CALABRESE KID was a bit slow into stride leaving the start and settled at the rear to begin, chased five wide along the turn, ran evenly in the stretch and did not threaten in the late stages. STRETCH RUN was a bit hard to load prior to the start, lunged at the break and was off a step slowly, rushed up in the early stages and tracked the quick pace from the inside, lost position while inside of rivals heading to the quarter marker, chased into the stretch and gave way in the final furlong.

ENTRY.NAME: Stretch Run
ENTRY.COMMENT: hard to load/lunged start,rushed up inside,chased,gave way

ENTRY.COMMENT: dipusted pace inside,took command 3/16,met late bid,dug in

ENTRY.COMMENT: bit slow into stride,settled,chased 5wd turn,no threat

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Pike Place Dancer S. GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 5 1M Turf CR: 89. Stakes Purse 75000. FOR FILLIES TWO YEARS OLD. By subscription of $50 each to accompany the nomination or by supplementary nomination of $2,000 at the time of entry which includes all fees. $500 to enter and $500 additional to start with $75,000 Guaranteed. Weight: 122 l bs. Maidens allowed 3 lbs. Highest earnings preferred. A trophy will be presented to the winning owner. Nominations closed Thursday, October 19, 2023 with 14 nominations.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CHARLENE'S DREAM was prominent away from the start and raced close up to the early pace, prompted the pace into the backstretch run then advanced to contest the pace to the half-mile pole, took command from TOUR QUEEN along the far turn and showed the way into upper stretch, was given a reminder tap and held foes at bay to the furlong marker, dug in under firm urging into the final sixteenth, repelled the bid of ANGIOLLETA in deep stretch and held in a drive to prevail. ANGIOLLETA (IRE) settled along the inside into the first turn, was taken off of the rail and tracked two wide along the backstretch run, raced three wide into the far turn and was roused four wide into the stretch, rallied approaching the furlong marker, responded to firm urging and came within aim at the the sixteenth-pole, was repelled by the winner in deep stretch and was outfinished, while holding safely for second in the end. SOHO tracked the moderate pace from the inside, saved ground into the far turn, was taken off of the rail and was roused two wide at the quarter pole, shifted to the three path into the stretch and vied for the lead approaching the furlong marker, needed more in deep stretch, was outkicked in the final sixteenth and held safely at the finish for third. TOUR QUEEN broke alertly and was forwardly placed early on, engaged with CHARLENE'S DREAM into the first turn and contested moderate fractions with that rival into the backstretch run, disputed the pace to the half-mile marker then lost position into the far turn, chased CHARLENE'S DREAM into the stretch and faded in the final stages. SUSIE CRU was unhurried to begin, raced three wide into the backstretch run and tracked to the half-mile marker, lost contact with the others along the far turn and chased three wide into the stretch, lacked a response in the drive and did not factor. KRISTIN LEE was forwardly placed in the early going, stalked the moderate pace from a two wide path into the backstretch run, gained ground heading to the half-mile marker and came three wide into the far turn, could not keep pace into the stretch and tired in the final furlong.

ENTRY.NAME: Tour Queen
ENTRY.OWNER: A Jason Hall Stables and Baker Stephen R

ENTRY.NAME: Charlene's Dream
ENTRY.COMMENT: close up,prompted pace,bid 2wd 3/8,dug in late,held driving

ENTRY.NAME: Angiolleta (IRE)
ENTRY.OWNER: Great Friends Stables LLC Cahill James F Davis Mark and Leatherman Ty

ENTRY.NAME: Soho
ENTRY.OWNER: Talla Racing LLC and West Point Thoroughbreds

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 6 1M All Weather Track CR: 108. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 32000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON $15,000 TWICE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR STATE BRED OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $62,500. Three Year Olds, 123 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since August 15 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $62,500 (Maiden, Claiming And Starter Races For $50,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TESORO tracked behind AMERICAN FARMER three wide through the first half mile, moved to challenge that one to the outside passing the half mile pole, had that bid rebuffed but regrouped mid-stretch, came back on and was able to reel in that stubborn rival the final yards. AMERICAN FARMER got away from the gate very quickly and was able to lead the field through a pedestrian first quarter, then got pressed by LMLOOKNFORMISCHIEF down the backstretch, kept that one at bay to the half mile marker then was challenged on the outside by TESORO, rebroke and held that rival at bay to deep stretch then was outfinished in the shadow of the wire. KENNEBEC hustled to get position going into the first turn, the settled three wide and kept close while under a bit of a hold, attempted to re-engage passing the three eighths pole then put in a late run down the middle of the track to grab third. NO ICE NO GLASS stumbled at the start, broke a bit behind the others, then was floated five wide into the first turn, got over to the inside for the backstretch run, raced near the back, rallied through the far turn, came into the stretch three wide then ran on well while chasing the top pair but was nailed at the wire for third. AMERICA GREAT broke inward at the break then got bounced around once clear of the gate, took to the rail and raced close up to the half mile marker then struggled to keep up when the pace quickened in the middle of the far turn and ran on evenly to the wire. FLASHIEST was held up near the rear of the field through the first half mile, set down passing the three furlong marker and attempted to rally but could do no better than chase the field home. LMLOOKNFORMISCHIEF broke alertly then steadied repeatedly through the first turn while between horses and hard to place, once clear pulled the rider to the lead then settled down approaching the half mile pole, could not go on with the top two when they quickened away with three furlongs to run, then had nothing to offer down the stretch.

ENTRY.OWNER: BKB Stables LLC and Sherman Steve
ENTRY.COMMENT: controlled pace, met bid 3/8, short lead, outfinished last jumps

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 7 5F Turf CR: 78. Maiden Claiming Purse 17000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 123 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000, if for $22,500, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: RESERVE PROOF was hustled leaving the break, showed good early speed and disputed the fast pace into the turn, dueled through fast fractions along the bend while inside of AS LUCK HAPPENS, continued that battle into the stretch and took a narrow lead at the furlong marker, kept to task while firmly handled into deep stretch, held the runner-up at bay in the final strides and determinedly prevailed. AS LUCK HAPPENS broke out leaving the start and crowded a neighboring rival, was prominent three wide in the early stages and pressed the fast pace into the turn, dueled outside of RESERVE PROOF heading to the quarter marker, continued that battle into the stretch, drifted out under firm urging in deep stretch, was held at bay by the determined winner in the final strides and held clearly in the end for second. TIGER TOO bobbled at the start, was away slowly and was unhurried in the early stages, saved ground into the turn and improved position heading to the quarter marker, made a steady gain into the stretch, sustained his rally through the drive, could not impact the top pair in the final stages but was gaining in deep stretch and was up in the final strides to secure third. JOHNNY PAYCHECK tracked the fast early pace while between runners, moved up three wide into the turn and gained ground nearing the quarter marker, was outkicked into the stretch, chased the top pair into the final sixteenth, did not offer a late response and was just edged for third at the finish. WESTERN SIERRA broke alertly and established the early lead, disputed the fast pace two wide between runners into the turn, lost position entering the bend and chased to the quarter marker, ran in pursuit to mid-stretch, could not muster a late response and weakened. SHAUN'S JAZZ was crowded by a neighboring rival at the start and was away a bit slowly, chased the fast pace from the outside, was coaxed along four wide into the stretch and did not threaten. R HEART OF GOLD chased the fast early pace from the inside, improved position along the turn, tipped two wide into the stretch, lost a bit of ground at the furlong marker and finished evenly. UNCLE DUSAN chased the fast early pace from the outside, slipped to the two path entering the turn, lost position at the quarter marker, raced three wide into the stretch and gave way. GONNA GETCHA GOOD took back off of the fast early pace, was green and hard to place in the first furlong, drifted out entering the turn and lost position inside of the three-furlong marker, trailed into the stretch and did not make a late impact.

ENTRY.NAME: Gonna Getcha Good
ENTRY.COMMENT: took back,green/hard to place,drifted out 3/8,no impact

ENTRY.NAME: Shaun's Jazz
ENTRY.OWNER: Victory Rose Thoroughbreds Inc and Ruvalcaba Alberto

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 8 5 1/2F All Weather Track CR: 76. Claiming Purse 15000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 123 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500, if for $10,500, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: RAVEN'S QUEST showed speed away from the gate, assumed command and set a pressured pace from the inside in the opening furlong, dueled along the turn with BOBBY'S GENIE and set a fast pace to the quarter pole, shook free into upper stretch and drew clear while in hand approaching the furlong marker, was given a pair of reminder urges into the final sixteenth, drew off in deep stretch and was hand ridden to the finish to be much the best. MO TOWN GAL tracked the fast early pace from the outside, came five wide into the turn, shifted to the four path heading to the quarter marker and improved position nearing the top of the stretch, was no match for the winner in the stretch drive but stayed on in the late stages and held safely at the finish for second. CRY ME A RUNNER tracked the fast early pace from the second flight, came in tight entering the turn and steadied behind a weakening rival while four wide, gained ground heading to the quarter marker, came in tight approaching the top of the lane and shifted in for the stretch drive, lacked the needed response in the stretch but stayed on in the final sixteenth and was up in time to claim third. CHIC SAMARAI chased from the second flight, improved position two wide on the turn, was urged along three wide into the stretch, could not muster a rally in the final furlong and was just edged for the third at the finish. BOBBY'S GENIE was hustled leaving the break and was prominent in the early running, pressed the fast pace outside of RAVEN'S QUEST, dueled outside of that rival into the turn and disputed the fast pace to the quarter pole, could not match strides into the stretch and faded in the late stages. BLUE EYED JO chased the fast early pace and lost position heading to the half-mile marker, raced in the three path into the turn, was asked for run four wide into the stretch, was able to improve position in the final furlong but failed to threaten. GETAWAY CHARM broke through the gate prior to the start, was forwardly placed in the early stages and chased the fast pace from the outside, gained ground three then two wide along the turn, could not keep pace into the stretch and tired in the final furlong. LISA'S VALENTINE was prominent in the early stages and raced close up to the fast early pace, lost position two wide along the turn, came three wide into the stretch and weakened. PATSY MONTANA was unprepared at the start and was away slowly, chased the fast pace from the inside, saved ground to the top of the stretch and did not factor.

ENTRY.COMMENT: showed speed inside,shook free 3/16,drew off stretch,much best

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 9 1 1/16M All Weather Track CR: 100. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 31000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON $15,000 ONCE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR STATE BRED OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $25,000. Three Year Olds, 123 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000 (Cal-Bred O r Cal-Sired Horses That Have Won The Open First Condition Allowance Race In Northern California Must Carry An Additional 2 lbs., Unless Entered for the Optional Claiming Price.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: A MAN'S MAN came away well, raced in hand up close with the early leaders through the clubhouse turn then stalked the slow pace being set by LAW ABIDING to the far turn, moved to challenge for the lead passing the quarter pole, met brief resistance at the head of the stretch, sprinted away at the furlong marker and won handily. MOOGIE SON settled inside well off the pace through the initial stages, bided time through the turn waiting for room, took advantage of a big hole up the rail into stretch, ran on well, tipped out a path near the eighth pole to get around a tiring LAW ABINDING but was no match for the winner. ECOLOGIST raced three wide through the first turn then worked into a forward tracking position while still wide down the backstretch, was put into a sustained drive from the seven-sixteenths pole, soldiered on down the middle of the track and just got up for third. RODRIGOKNOWS was able to get good forward and inside position behind the pacesetter into the first turn, bided time inside just off the leader to the far turn, came under pressure near the five-sixteenths pole, had a mild response but could not summon another gear when needed. BUENISIMO broke a step slow then was hustled to keep in contact with the pack, then was content to settle near the back of the field, tried to rally through the far turn, became stuck behind horses as the field bunched up, found some room along the rail into the stretch and was able to improve position in the late stages. HOUSE OF LORDS raced mid-pack between horses to the far turn, moved closer in tight quarters going into the turn, waited for room through the turn, attempted to rally inside under urging but lacked the needed response. COUSIN RICHIE raced near the rear of the field and three wide through the first half of the race, started a mild rally while still three wide on the far turn then swung five wide into the stretch and finished with some gain on the outside of the group behind the top pair. HARMON lacked any speed from the gate and lagged at the rear of the field, could not keep up through the far turn when the pace quickened, came under a ride but did not offer up a response. LAW ABIDING broke best and came away with the lead going into the first turn, held sway through the turn, was challenged by A MAN'S MAN near the quarter pole, battled back briefly to mid-stretch then was spent and passed by the entire field in the final furlong.
